    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using characters that use multiple bytes, eg: `ðŸ˜€` (4 bytes), this will count as 4 _columns_ within treesitter, making `get_node_range()` return an incorrect columns\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim +'i|# ðŸ˜€' +InspectTree --clean test.md\n\n\"observe `heading_content: (inline)` is reported as 4 columns wide when it should be 1\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect that the documentation reflect that tree sitter ranges are in bytes, not columns, or that treesitter ranges should be in columns not bytes.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-1539+gb75a68ff06\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.25.0-3-g55876044\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\naur (neovim-git)",
